  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds options for creating an XPS document.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKDocumentXpsOptions` holds configuration options used when creating an XPS document
via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKDocument.CreateXps(System.String,SkiaSharp.SKDocumentXpsOptions)>.
Use it to control the output resolution and whether PNG image data is required.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var options = new SKDocumentXpsOptions
{
    DPI = 300,
    AllowNoPngs = false,
};

using var document = SKDocument.CreateXps("output.xps", options);
using var canvas = document.BeginPage(595, 842);
canvas.DrawText("Hello, XPS!", 100, 100, new SKPaint());
document.EndPage();
```
]]></format></remarks>
